{"ts":"2026-06-27T08:55:43.532Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"ycg9pt4h","input":{"summary":"I have performed a thorough accessibility, UI polish, and functional check of the login portal and admin workspace. \n\nHere is a summary of the work reviewed, verified, and polished:\n1. **Semantic HTML Structures**: Corrected and verified container divisions to semantic landmarks such as `<main>` for primary portal forms and `<nav>` for bottom navigation menus, aiding screen reader context.\n2. **Interactive Controls & Focus Indicators**: Ensured all custom components, including simulation role selections and telemetry panels, use correct `<button>` or interactive tags instead of bare passive divs. Focus outlines (`focus:ring-1 focus:ring-[#009DFF]`) have been consistently applied across the workspace to make tab-navigation perfectly clear.\n3. **WAI-ARIA Attributes**: Added screen reader descriptions via `aria-label`, `aria-expanded`, and `aria-haspopup` to clarify dynamic states on panels like notifications, workspace switches, role preview selectors, and mobile hamburger controls.\n4. **Form Association**: Tied all form inputs strictly to their respective semantic labels using `htmlFor` and unique element `id` connections. Added helper text and screen-reader only `sr-only` descriptions where visual labels are intentionally minimal to maintain GFF's ultra-premium sleek aesthetic.\n5. **Keyboard Handlers**: Verified keyboard events such as `Escape` mapping to close recovery and support modals, and `Enter/Space` mapping to column header sorts on data tables.\n6. **Robustness & Compatibility Verification**: Successfully ran TypeScript compilation (`npx tsc --noEmit`), ESLint checks, and tool-logic suite (`npm run verify-tools`) with 0 errors or warnings. Mobile layouts and dark-premium design principles have been fully preserved without breaking changes.","verified":true}}}
